    "postId" : "806751",
    "author" : {
      "username" : "1959bus",
      "userId" : "806751",
      "joined" : "Tue Sep 09, 2014 7:36 pm",
      "profileRank" : "Registered user",
      "location" : "-",
      "postCount" : "72",
      "avatarPath" : null
    },
    "content" : "Overall not too bad I think (I hope!) but the van does seem to have had a hard life as there is not a straight panel on it -apart from the fuel filler flap. The blaster said that it had had a lot of work done on it over the years and he dug out a lot of filler. The chassis seems pretty good and the wheel arches are still intact, gutters are OK too.\n<br> \n<br>One question if I may - where to begin?! It needs a new cargo floor and sills + long and short panels so I was going to lift the floor first, clean repair any rot to chassis that needs sorting, new inner sills and then the floor back down before moving to remove the long and short panels? I’m not sure of the best order of service!\n<br>\n<br>The long and short panels have been attacked with an angle grinder around the arches so this along the state of the sills has led me to believe it’s better to replace the lot.",
    "lastEdited" : "Wed Oct 15, 2014 7:33 am"
  }, {
    "postId" : "806805",
    "author" : {
      "username" : "pokey",
      "userId" : "806805",
